Cape Town - EFF leader Julius Malema and his wife Mantwa Matlala have added another young freedom fighter to their family. Malema announced on Instagram on Wednesday that his wife had given birth to a baby boy who the couple have named Kopano.  Bana ba mberengwa, tšhipi ya bokgalaka, congratulations mma go Bašimane. It’s a boy, his name is Kopano.🍼🍼 A post shared by  Juliusmalemasello (@julius.malema.sello) on Feb 7, 2018 at 12:13am PST  The couple have another son, Munzhedzi, who was born in October 2016. The baby was kept out of the public eye for a full year before his proud father posted a picture on Instagram.  Ladies and gentlemen meet the one and only Fighter Munzhedzi Malema of the Mašupatsela a Economic Freedom Fighters. 🕺🏽🙌🏿💃🏿♥️✊🏿 A post shared by  Juliusmalemasello (@julius.malema.sello) on Nov 28, 2017 at 11:27am PST  Juju also has an older son named Ratanang from a previous relationship. IOL